The Progressive Yoruba Youth Congress (PYYC) has appealed to Nigerians to always appreciate efforts of the Nigerian Armed Forces in tackling insurgents, just as it stated that the enormous sacrifices of officers and soldiers in the war front against the terrorists should be appreciated. Briefing the press in Lagos, the group said the Nigerian military has turned the tide against the Boko Haram/ISWAP terrorists since 2016 and they deserve maximum support of Nigerians. The group said it is uncharitable for anybody, group or organisation to castigate the arm forces for not being proactive in dealing with the insurgents. The group also condemned the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) for heating up the polity through unguarded statements credited to its leadership. According to a statement issued by the group and jointly signed by its president and secretary, Elder Kola Salawu and Majekodunmi Omolola, respectively, it commended President Muhammadu Buhari for providing the necessary succour to the military. The group explained that what CAN did is capable of dividing the nation and demoralising the troops. It said the Christian body should not be seen as partisan, but noted that statements credited  to  its leadership of recent portrayed the body in bad light. It noted that the unguided statements credited to CAN are counter-productive in the fight against terrorism and capable of pitching the Christians against the Muslims. The group said that anybody that fails to recognise the remarkable sacrifices of the military in the war front does not have the interest of the country at heart.  